main event: Two unidentified flying object sightings were reported in Harrisburg, Pennsylvania - one on April 18, 1955, and the other on April 6, 1955.
interesting points: The first sighting described a 33-inch square, silver object fluttering and drifting away, indicating a kite or debris. The conclusion was marked as 'Unknown'.
The second sighting reported an elongated, cigar-shaped object traveling at a rapid rate of speed, observed for approximately 2 minutes. No further information was available, and the case was closed.
Both sightings were categorized as 'Unknown' in terms of identifying the objects.
The documents and reports do not mention any photographs or images of the reported sightings.
The reports contain handwritten text and redacted or obscured information, possibly related to Project Blue Book, a program to investigate UFOs by the United States Air Force.
sighted object: 33-inch square silver object, elongated cigar-shaped object
